A violin reputedly played by the
bandmaster on the Titanic as the liner sank has been sold for
900,000 pounds ($1.46m) at auction in Wiltshire, south England,
today, the  BBC  reported.  The instrument, which is believed to have been played by
Wallace Hartley, had a guide price of 300,000 pounds.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
